Create `packages/schemas/src/common/query-helpers.ts` with the `queryBooleanParam()` function that correctly parses boolean query string params (fixing `z.coerce.boolean()` bug where `"false"` becomes `true`). Export from `packages/schemas/src/common/index.ts`.

Implementation:
```ts
export function queryBooleanParam() {
    return z.preprocess(
        (val) => {
            if (val === undefined || val === null || val === '') return undefined;
            return val === 'true' || val === true || val === '1';
        },
        z.boolean()
    ).optional();
}
```

